PDC is coordinating with state and local emergency management authorities across the Hawaiian Islands as a powerful, slow-moving “Kona Low” storm northwest of the islands begins making landfall. 

The storm system will bring a prolonged period of hazardous weather across the state beginning today and through the upcoming weekend. Periods of heavy rain are expected, with potential for severe flash flooding, damaging winds, and strong to severe thunderstorms. Severe weather may result in hail and/or tornado activity. 

Based on current model forecasts, this potentially life-threatening weather pattern will continue to unfold across Hawaii into early next week. 

State and local decision makers are encouraged to log in to PDC’s DisasterAWARE platform to assess potential flood impacts and exposure of critical infrastructure to storm impacts, visualize 3-day cumulative rainfall forecasts, and monitor storm impacts in real time via live cameras. 

>> Visit https://disasteraware.pdc.org 

The public is encouraged to download PDC’s Disaster Alert mobile app for real-time updates on the storm, as well as for flood zone information and cumulative rainfall forecasts.

>> Download Disaster Alert on the App Store and Google Play 

